Police in Lugari subcounty are holding a middle-aged man for allegedly killing his friend in what is believed to be a love triangle. Lugari subcounty police commander Bernard Ngungu said the suspect reportedly stabbed the man to death on suspicion that he (the deceased) was having an affair with his wife. He said preliminary investigations revealed that the suspect from Lukhuna village, Mbagara sublocation, picked a quarrel with the deceased before the argument turned violent. The suspect picked a kitchen knife and stabbed his friend in the chest, killing him on the spot. The suspect tried to flee, but he was cornered and arrested by villagers, who handed him to police. The police boss said the suspect is being held at Lumakanda police station as investigations continue. Police moved the body to Kimbilio Funeral Home in Uasin Gishu county.  